article.headline: James Madison 59, La Salle 50
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Ray Barbosa scored 18 points and Jomo Belfor added 10 as James Madison defeated La Salle 59-50 on Saturday in the season opener for both teams. Steven Smith had 17 points for La Salle, which has a roster including six freshmen and three walk-ons. Three prominent players from last year's team are no longer in school as a result of sexual assault charges. The Dukes led by 10 points twice in the second half before the Explorers rallied to within 47-45 on a layup by Lewis Fadipe with 4:54 to play. James Madison then ran off eight straight points, capped by a steal and layup by Belfor to seal the win. La Salle connected on only 16-of-54 shots (29.6 percent) in the game, including 6-of-28 shots (21.4 percent) in the second half. Barbosa scored 10 points as the Dukes jumped out to an early 18-8 lead, but La Salle then scored nine in a row, and behind Smith's 13 points trailed by only 28-26 at halftime. Both teams were led by new head coaches. La Salle's John Giannini replaced Billy Hahn, who resigned in the wake of the sex-assault charges against his players. James Madison's Dean Keener was hired to replace Sherman Dillard, who was forced to resign after seven mostly uninspiring seasons.
